The paper deals with lower bounds for dimensionality reducing linear maps, which are relevant to several areas of computer science. The use of the Johnson-Lindenstrauss lemma and the restricted isometry property suggest that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The focus on sparsity and dimensionality reduction also suggests the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the use of matrix properties and linear algebra suggests the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
